result.name: Silencio

reviews.text: Food is excellent. Must go and try. But service needs to improve. Hardly desirable having haul down attention, especially when there was not many guests around
Great new contemporary izakaya concept. Really liked the ambiance of live music. Great food and sake selections as well!

Never know that lily n bloom changed to this restaurant until my friend showed me a week ago and went for a dinner to try out their food! 
Once I walked in, i am already amazed by the artwork and the jazz band! 
Food wise, I love all the dishes we had on the night, esp one of the dishes called Kim Jun which is with pear and kimchi, its flavour is really interesting and match very well. They also has really great sake list to match with the dishes, will go back with bigger group so can try more dishes and sake next time!!

Highly recommended if you love Japanese food and live music! I visited Silencio last week with my friend and we both had a great experience, both the food and service were excellent! Will definitely go back again!

Definitely recommend going to SILENCIO if you love Japanese food! The food at this beautiful new restaurant is just delightful. The live band was fantastic and the staff was friendly, polite and very professional. I will be coming back soon.
